<TEXT>
charles vest provost of the university 
of michigan has been named president of the massachusetts 
institute of technology a post he called one of the greatest 
bully pulpits in science 
the 48yearold mechanical engineer was elected unanimously 
monday by the mit corporation the schools governing body 
the selection of the schools 15th president ends a trying 
yearlong effort to replace the retiring paul gray in which three 
leading candidates withdrew 
vest will be leaving a statesupported university with 50000 
students on three campuses for a private research institution with 
9700 students mit founded in 1861 has long ranked among the 
worlds finest universities 
the presidency of mit is one of the greatest bully pulpits for 
science and technology in the united states and i will make use of 
it vest said monday 
in a statement vest said mit will lead in the redefinition 
of engineering education in light of scientific change and the new 
global and social realities 
vest said the training of engineers needs to be expanded to 
include more exposure to the humanities and other areas 
mit has long performed research for the pentagon and vest said 
he expects that to continue but as defense needs diminish vest 
said he hopes more researchers can devote themselves to fields such 
as manufacturing health and biotechnology 
the choice of the softspoken vest was praised at mit and at ann 
arbor where vest arrived from his native west virginia as a 
graduate student in 1963 and went on to become dean of engineering 
and in 1989 provost 
mit made the right choice said james duderstadt president 
of the university of michigan 
vest has extraordinary vision and depth and that rare 
ability to get people to do things by believing they want to do 
them duderstadt said 
gray said in march 1989 that he intended to step down next month 
after 10 years and become mit corporation chairman 
the frontrunner for president mit provost david deutch 
withdrew after his nomination drew strong opposition from some 
faculty 
nobel laureate and mit biologist david baltimore was viewed as 
the probable best alternative to deutch but he took a job as 
president of rockefeller university 
in february mit professor phillip sharp said he would take the 
job but before the mit corporation had a chance to vote on him he 
had a change of heart sharp said he preferred to continue his 
cancer research and teaching 
</TEXT>
