<TEXT>
the vice rector of huancayo university a 
marxist who taught philosophy and literature was murdered along 
with his driver and their bodies were found 10 days after they were 
abducted family members say 
the bodies of jaime cerron and armando tapia were found monday 
by farmers in a ravine outside this andean city 120 miles east of 
lima according to cerrons widow bertha 
she said both men had their hands tied and were shot in the 
head and that the hands and feet of cerron showed signs of torture 
cerron and tapia were kidnapped 10 days ago by six heavilyarmed 
men who stopped the pickup truck in which the two were travelling 
witnesses said the kidnappers may have been soldiers dressed in 
civilian clothes military officials would not comment on the case 
cerron had been arrested six months ago for supposed contacts 
with maoist shining path guerrillas mrs cerron said he was soon 
released she said 
more than 18500 people have died in political violence since 
the shining path took up arms 10 years ago 
