scandalplagued housing and urban development programs of the past 
20 years administration officials indicated a willingness to 
accept 3 billion more in spending on housing than it wanted but 
only on condition 
budget director richard darman said the administration wants 
sections of the bill rewritten to assure that new construction of 
public housing is deemphasized in favor of renovating and 
preserving the current stock of dilapidated and unused units 
it also wants stronger language on targeting the new aid to the 
poor rather than middleincome families and it seeks a requirement 
that buyers using federal housing administrationbacked mortgages 
put up more of their own money in the closing costs as a 
disincentive for walking away from the loans 
