market cranston said we believe we can avoid that and still 
assure that the fund remains actuarially sound 
the fha lost 42 billion to bad loans in 1988 and now has a net 
worth of only 26 billion compared with 8 billion in 1979 
if housing prices which are now flat or falling in much of the 
country dont rise at least 4 percent a year the fha insurance 
fund will require an infusion of tax dollars to remain afloat the 
congressional general accounting office said earlier this month 
