his wife winnie instead attended for him 
we are on the threshold of major change in south africa he 
told the crowd we are confident that victory is in sight but as 
in a steeplechase race the last hurdles are the most difficult to 
jump 
earlier monday mandela addressed canadas parliament and called 
for maintaining economic sanctions against south africa to ensure 
that reforms continue 
any move at this stage toward lifting or lessening 
international pressure would create a situation in which the white 
minority would feel comfortable with the minimal changes which have 
taken place mandela told a joint session of the house of commons 
and the senate 
canada imposed economic and political sanctions on south africa 
in 1986 like many other countries it has pledged to maintain the 
bans until there is clear evidence of irreversible change in the 
apartheid system of racial segregation 
president fw de klerk of south africa has argued that the 
reforms show that his country is changing and he has urged foreign 
countries to lift economic sanctions 
in his speech mandela paid tribute to black south africans who 
during years of oppression met torture without flinching and 
met the hangmans noose with songs of freedom 
he was interrupted several times by applause and received a long 
standing ovation from lawmakers 
mandela is in the midst of a sixweek tour of 14 nations in 
africa europe and north america that began june 6 he was freed 
from prison in february after serving 27 years of a life sentence 
for sabotage and plotting to overthrow the whiteminority 
government 
his release was part of a program of social reforms by the de 
klerk government including legalizing the anc and other 
antiapartheid groups 
