<TEXT>
president corazon aquino has turned 
to a formula once used by her discredited predecessor in order to 
revive the people power spirit that propelled her to office 
last week mrs aquino unveiled plans for a nationwide movement 
to channel government private business and volunteer organizations 
to deliver basic services and improve lives of millions of 
impoverished filipinos 
the plan is to bypass traditional politicians in congress 
and the bureaucracy those institutions have blocked many of the 
grandiose plans for reform promised but not delivered by the 
4yearold aquino government 
for the movement mrs aquino chose the name kabisig a 
tagalog word for people locked arminarm she cited the spirit 
of the 1986 uprising against ferdinand marcos when hundreds of 
thousands of filipinos stood arminarm to block tanks seeking to 
crush a military mutiny against the late president 
were fasttracking all of corys priorities said transport 
secretary oscar orbos a former congressman and leading figure in 
kabisig 
the roman catholic magazine veritas said kabisig was 
designed to circumvent traditional centers of power and the 
sluggish energy and timeconsuming bureaucracy grown fat and 
complacent with inaction 
mrs aquino hopes to bring into the movement the social activist 
groups human rights organizations and labor federations that stood 
at the forefront of the struggle against marcos those groups have 
been largely disillusioned with mrs aquinos failure to institute 
reforms after the people power revolution 
at the same time the kabisig movement has drawn fire from 
proaquino politicians 
there were statements in corys speech which made me feel 
insecure forlorn dejected and rejected said sen rene 
