use of socalled nonpolitical mass movements is a 
timetested formula for bypassing established parties after 
declaring martial law in 1972 marcos banned political parties 
then organized various grassroots organizations ostensibly to 
invigorate and transform philippine society 
his most successful venture was the new society movement which 
evolved into a megaparty similar to the largely defunct communist 
organizations that once held sway in eastern europe 
for years mrs aquino has excused the shortcomings of her 
administration by claiming that inefficiency was the price of 
democracy after 20 years of marcos tyranny 
she pointed proudly to her new constitution and elected 
bicameral legislature as examples of her restored democracy 
ironically at a time when surveys show her popularity declining 
mrs aquino is now bypassing those institutions to deliver reforms 
she already has the entire government machinery at her beck 
and call wrote columnist emil jurado in the manila standard 
what reason would she havefor depending on cory loyalists and 
nongovernment organizations for the survival of her 
