the state and us governments have filed a 
lawsuit that accuses eight companies of toxic dumping in california 
waters and takes the unusual step of trying to force industry to 
return the area to the way it was 
the lawsuit filed monday in federal court contends the 
companies dumped hundreds of tons of such chemicals as ddt and pcbs 
since the mid1940s harming fisheries and births of the bald 
eagle peregrine falcon and sea lion 
lawyers called the lawsuit unique 
in the past the state recovered funds for cleanup of ocean 
dumping but theres never been an attempt to collect money to 
