or survivors just as the 1952 reparations agreement with west 
germany known as the luxembourg agreement did not address that 
issue steinberg said 
the luxembourg agreement which will serve as the model for the 
talks with east germany only covered west german payments to 
israel and jewish institutions the west german parliament later 
passed a law providing for compensation of individual claims 
