<TEXT>
an israeli arab poet was placed under house 
arrest tuesday and faces trial on charges that his poems about the 
palestinian uprising incite violence by arabs against jews 
shafik habib is the first israeli arab author to be prosecuted 
for his writing 
this is a very serious move against an arab intellectual this 
lit up a red light for all of us said habib a father of six who 
lives in the northern israeli village of deir hanna 
police claimed after habibs arrest last week that in a 
collection of poems titled return to the future he calls for 
the continuation of the uprising and appeals to arabs to use 
firearms and kill the jews 
judge eitan magen on tuesday ordered habib placed under house 
arrest after he was charged with identifying with a terror group 
through his writing israelis usually mean the plo when they refer 
an unspecified terror organization 
magen said habib must stay at home until further hearings could 
be held on a police request that he be jailed until trial no trial 
date was scheduled 
the israeli news agency itim said habibs passport was seized 
and he was ordered to pay a bond of 5000 
the charges against habib come at a time of growing 
identification among israels 810000 arab citizens with the 
antiisraeli revolt of their 17 million brethren living in the 
occupied west bank and gaza strip 
last month after an israeli gunman killed seven palestinian 
laborers rioting erupted in many arab towns and villages within 
israel police responded with tear gas and rubber bullets tactics 
they frequently use in the occupied lands but rarely in israel 
there are many close ties between israeli arabs and those in the 
territories many in the territories fled from homes that fell 
under israeli control at the founding of the jewish state in 1948 
habib who defines himself as a palestinian arab living in 
israel said he used to write love poems until the uprising began 
in december 1987 
anger over the methods used to crush the revolt prompted him to 
change subjects 
in one of his poems news bulletin he writes about alleged 
army brutality 
the commander has issued an urgent order break arms and 
legs smash necks crush skulls and chase them leave them as 
corpses rotting in the soil 
but he denies his work incites violence 
i see something on television and i write a poem about it 
but its impossible to encourage stonethrowing and i know not to 
cross the red line im a responsible person he said in a 
telephone interview from his home 
habib also argued that all the poems in the return to the 
future collection had previously been published by israeli arab 
newspapers which are subject to censorship 
the army routinely reviews material submitted to arabiclanguage 
newspapers in israel and the occupied lands and it frequently bans 
publication of items 
israeli arab leaders said the charges against habib violated 
free speech and contradicted prime minister yitzhak shamirs pledge 
that his new rightwing government would seek peace 
this regime is very weak if they are afraid of words we are 
not talking about stones or bombs said legislator abdul wahab 
darousha 
