<TEXT>
rival christian forces fought with 
howitzers and mortars across the christian enclave tuesday in a 
confrontation that killed four people and was the most serious 
violation of monthold ceasefire 
police said six people were injured in the battles which began 
at 945 am and subsided five hours later a french government 
envoy francois scheer met in west beirut with president elias 
hrawi in an effort to salvage a vatican plan for ending the 
christian warfare 
the new casualties raised the overall toll to 1040 killed and 
2780 wounded since the battle for control of the christian enclave 
erupted jan 30 the fighting is between troops of gen michel aoun 
and militiamen of samir geageas lebanese forces a ceasefire was 
declared may 17 
the latest battles covered most of the 310squaremile christian 
enclave the streets of east beirut and the surrounding hinterland 
were deserted as people huddled in basements and bomb shelters 
a police spokesman said it could not be determined who started 
the clashes but noted that tension had been mounting since monday 
when lebanons president rejected a vatican proposal for a 
permanent settlement to the conflict 
the vatican has suggested reconsideration of an accord designed 
to end lebanons 15yearold civil war it was that accord 
supported by the arab league that led to hrawis election as 
president 
in return for reconsidering the accord aoun would agree to 
recognize hrawis government the vatican suggested 
prime minister salim hoss and parliament speaker hussein 
husseini backed hrawi in his opposition to the idea 
the french government is helping lebanon to overcome the 
difficulties it is facing scheer told reporters after the 
90minute meeting with hrawi the dialogue led by france could 
help support the mechanism of the taif accord scheer added 
referring to the saudi arabian city in which the accord was reached 
scheer said he also planned to meet the vatican ambassador while 
in lebanon the ambassador papal nuncio pablo puente met tuesday 
with aoun at the generals headquarters outside beirut we are 
seeking peace through peace puente told reporters after the 
meeting 
france and the vatican have been the christians main backers 
since lebanons independence from france in 1943 neighboring syria 
backs the moslems 
the conservative newspaper addiyar reported tuesday that scheer 
was promoting a fivepoint compromise plan that called for 
recognition of the hrawi government by all the warring factions in 
addition to recognizing the taif accord as a frame for a national 
settlement 
the compromise also called for the formation of an expanded 
national government respresenting all the factions this echoed 
the vaticans suggestion that aoun be given a government portfolio 
the french proposal according to the report said the taif 
accord should be debated in parliament and the decision on passing 
or rejecting it should be left to the house 
it called for parliamentary elections as soon as possible 
the newspaper added 
aoun has rejected the taif agreement because it does not include 
a deadline for the withdrawal of syrian soldiers from lebanon 
syria has about 40000 troops in lebanon under a 1976 mandate to 
quell civil war fighting but aoun maintains they violated that 
mandate by siding with the moslems in the war 
