she has not asked for asylum she is just my guest said the 
diplomat a key western critic of romanias human rights record 
under ceausescu 
the government reacted sharply to the development 
munteanu is not a political prisoner but a criminal it said 
in a statement we have nothing against his wife and we are 
astounded that she chose the dutch embassy asking for refuge 
the interior ministry suggested most of the 1021 people 
detained last week had been set free it said in a statement that 
69 had been charged with major crimes and 182 with petty crimes 
state television said the violence last week caused 75 million 
in damage 
foreign governments including the united states have condemned 
the way romania has handled protests and numerous countries have 
suspended all but humanitarian aid 
stork warned against drawing parallels between the iliescu 
governments behavior and the brutal suppression of dissent under 
ceausescu 
theres a little flurry of human rights cases now he said 
its not to be confused with the previous period in those days 
people didnt dare to ask for help from western embassies 
the opposition romania libera daily published tuesday for the 
first time since miners shut the paper down thursday but copies of 
the 800000circulation daily were difficult to find 
editor mihai creanga suggested there were some hitches in 
publishing but refused to elaborate 
in an editorial the paper indirectly criticized the 
antigovernment rioting and iliescus use of miners to crush the 
opposition 
in a democratic state there is no room for instigation to 
violence because as we know violence breeds violence the 
daily said 
in paris the international federation of newspaper publishers 
protested tuesday to iliescu over attacks on members of the staff 
and offices of the newspaper 
