<TEXT>
a woman who ran a boardinghouse was 
ordered tuesday to stand trial on nine murder counts for allegedly 
poisoning her mostly elderly tenants to get their pension and 
disability benefits 
dorothea puente 61 was ordered to be arraigned july 10 in 
sacramento county superior court the order by county municipal 
court judge gail ohanesian culminated a five week preliminary 
hearing 
i do find that there is ample circumstantial evidence that 
death was by criminal means the judge said adding that there 
was sufficient evidence that puente had the opportunity to kill 
for financial gain 
puente who has displayed little emotion throughout her hearing 
sat quietly at the defense table 
puente was orderd to stand trial on all the counts with which 
she had been charged she could face the death penalty if convicted 
prosecutors said her murder trial could last at least six months 
she has pleaded innocent and defense attorneys insisted she 
would be aquitted 
there is totally insufficient evidence to convict her or 
anybody else based on the quality of evidence that has been 
presented in court in this case assistant public defender kevin 
clymo said 
puente was arrested after a social worker complained that one of 
her clients a roomer in puentes downtown home had disappeared 
in november 1988 authorities dug up seven bodies from the grounds 
of the victorianstyle dwelling 
she was later implicated in two other deaths that of a woman 
who died of a drug overdose at puentes house and that of a man 
whose body was found in a wooden box in a neighboring county 
prosecutors said puente has a record of administering stupefying 
drugs to intended robbery victims they contend the matronly 
exconvict killed her victims for their social security and 
government benefit checks 
defense attorneys said the alleged victims ranging from age 52 
to 80 and mostly poor and alcoholic died either by suicide or 
natural causes among their ailments were a brain tumor lung 
disease heart disease and diabetes 
the preliminary hearing featured 17 days of testimony by nearly 
80 witnesses and more than 100 exhibits much of the testimony 
focused on the causes of death 
in only one death the first one was a cause ever listed ruth 
munroe 61 died april 28 1982 from an overdose of codeine and 
tylenol that death was considered to be either accidental or a 
suicide until investigators began digging up bodies from the yard 
a prescription tranquilizer flurazepam or dalmane was detected 
in all seven bodies that had been buried in shallow graves on the 
boardinghouse grounds 
the medications role if any in the deaths is unclear the 
bodies buried anywhere from weeks to years were too decomposed 
for autopsies to determine the cause of deaths 
a total of nine other drugs were found in the boardinghouse 
bodies all seven people had been puentes tenants and their 
doctors and fellow boarders have testified that most of them were 
heavy drinkers 
the ninth murder charge was filed in connection with the death 
of everson theodore gillmouth a 77yearold oregon man who was 
puentes fiance and roommate when he died his body was found by 
fishermen on new years day 1986 in a wooden box on a bank of the 
sacramento river in sutter county 
