nearly 15000 polish officers in ostashkov and two other prison 
camps the crime became known as the katyn massacre when more than 
4200 bodies of polish officers were discovered in 1943 in the 
forest at katyn 
but the burial sites of the rest the elite of polish society 
called up from the reserves and captured after the red army invaded 
eastern poland in september 1939 remained a mystery 
