here is a brief chronological look at the progress of reform in 
south africas apartheid system of racial separation 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
sept 6 president f w de klerk launches a series of reforms 
allowing peaceful demonstrations and the opening of segregated 
beaches 
oct 15 six african national congress leaders imprisoned for 
more than 25 years including walter sisulu are released two 
weeks later the first legal anc rally in 30 years is held 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
feb 2 president de klerk legalizes the anc and more than 60 
other opposition groups suspends the death penalty and eases 
emergency restrictions 
feb 11 nelson mandela is released after serving 27 years in 
prison 
may 24 the anc and the south african government hold their 
first talks and agree to work together to end violence and 
negotiate a new constitution 
june 7 president de klerk ends the national state of 
emergency except in violencetorn natal province 
june 19 president de klerk repeals the separate amenities act 
the act passed in 1953 gave governments and privately owned 
enterprises the right to reserve facilities for whites such as 
parks hotels swimming pools toilets and recreation centers 
