a federal grand jury on tuesday indicted the 
retired head of the us food and drug administrations generic 
drug division on two counts of perjury in a corruption scandal 
involving the division 
the indictment accuses marvin seife of lying to government 
investigators about meetings with genericdrug company executives 
and about whether he let them buy him meals said us attorney 
breckinridge willcox 
seife who prosecutors said lives in san antonio did not have a 
telephone listing in that area his lawyers name was not available 
fda spokeswoman faye peterson said the agency had not seen the 
indictment and declined to comment 
the indictment was the latest development in the investigation 
into corruption in the genericdrug industry and among its 
regulators which began in the summer of 1988 
so far four of seifes former subordinates have been convicted 
on corruption and racketeering charges five genericdrug company 
executives three pharmaceutical companies and one industry 
consultant have been convicted on similar charges 
seife 66 retired dec 31 after 17 years as director of the 
genericdrug division where he was responsible for reviewing 
manufacturers applications to market generic drugs to the public 
according to the indictment seife gave a sworn statement oct 
25 to an fda investigator in which he falsely denied meeting with 
two genericdrug company executives on dec 11 1987 to discuss 
fda matters 
the indictment alleges that seife made a similar false statement 
july 11 to the house of representatives subcommittee on oversight 
and investigations 
the second count of the indictment charges that siefe also lied 
in the statement to fda investigators when he said i have made 
it a practice never to have meals with the regulated industry 
the indictment alleges seife accepted numerous lunches dinners and 
drinks paid for by genericdrug companies 
if convicted on both counts seife faces a maximum of 10 years 
in prison and a 500000 fine 
the case has been handled by federal prosecutors in baltimore 
because the fdas headquarters are in rockville 
