the united states has agreed to return to japan 
2500 acres of land used by the us military on the southern 
japanese island of okinawa officials said tuesday 
the timetable for the return of the land is subject to 
negotiations and further discussions by the two governments the 
japanese foreign ministry announced 
an interim report from the usjapan joint committee on 
realignment and consolidation of us forces facilities on okinawa 
said the land is in 23 sites 
the land being returned makes up 25 percent of the 62000 acres 
used by us military bases on okinawa a us territory from 1945 
until its reversion to japan in 1972 
american bases take up 20 percent of okinawa prefectures or 
states main island and until the mid1970s was okinawas main 
source of income 
