<TEXT>
the move toward offhours trading to compete 
with foreign exchanges got another boost as three exchanges agreed 
to cooperate on a computerized system to trade stock and stock 
options through the night 
the american stock exchange the chicago board options exchange 
and the cincinnati stock exchange on monday announced plans to 
implement an automated nighttime system in two to three years 
the new york stock exchange announced a different afterhours 
plan last week london and tokyo have been getting more of the 
business in uslisted issues while markets in this country are 
closed 
this agreement is a milestone in the internationalization of 
securities markets and we welcome other securities exchanges to 
join us in this endeavor said duke chapman chairman and chief 
executive of the cboe 
officials of the exchanges speaking at simultaneous news 
conferences in new york and chicago linked by television said they 
had asked the nyse and tokyo exchanges to join them but the big 
board indicated it didnt want to give up its leading role in us 
stocks 
the new york stock exchange today has the largest most cost 
efficient computer system in the world and we would like to invite 
the cboe and amex into our system which was announced last 
week said nyse spokesman richard torrenzano 
the amex cboe and cincinnati exchange plan to operate their 
electronic trading system between 6 pm and 6 am eastern time 
stocks now trade from 930 am to 4 pm and options from 930 
am until 410 pm or 415 pm 
the cboe would build and maintain the electronic exchanges main 
computer while reuters holdings plc would provide the network to 
link dealers with the computer 
reuters currently provides electronic dealing networks for 
foreiggn exchange and bond dealers and also is a leading supplier 
of financial market news 
the cboe and amex would provide a market in their stock options 
while the cincinnati exchange would offer stocks listed on that 
regional exchange 
the new york stock exchange last week revealed plans to begin 
limited afterhours trading this year with an eye to 24hour 
trading by the end of the decade the plan calls for thricenightly 
auctions of big boardlisted stocks at 8 pm midnight and 5 am 
beginning next year 
the deal announced monday represents a major cooperative effort 
at a time when competition is heating up among exchanges that 
handle stock options a new federal rule allows for multiple 
listings of stock options which now are assigned to particular 
exchanges 
under the computerized nighttime system the marketplace that 
establishes itself as the primary exchange for a particular issue 
will handle the stock option in the afterhours session 
the american stock exchange and the chicago board options 
exchange will still compete jones said but he conceded in 
the newly carvedout trading hours we will put aside some of 
todays competitive battles 
the precise number of issues that will be traded have yet to be 
determined the cincinnati exchange trades about 500 issues while 
the american exchange and cboe account for about 80 percent of the 
nations options trading 
the exchange executives said it was possible that other 
products such as stock index options could be traded through the 
system 
the cboe and amex would have to agree to make their products 
available said richard dufour the executive vice president for 
product development at the cboe well choose products that are 
most attractive to overseas customers 
options are financial instruments that give holders that right 
to buy or sell 100 shares of a stock at a designated price for a 
certain amount of time the three exchanges and reuters announced 
their intention to work on a common system in march 1989 they said 
they reached a definitive agreement about a month ago and the 
boards of the companies finished approving the plan late last week 
