natural gas vehicle marketing development manager for southern 
california gas this could be part of a much larger effort 
because of its environmental advantages over oilbased fuels 
natural gas has in the past year won the favor of congress and 
several state legislatures which have passed laws requiring use of 
the fuel in some of the nations most polluted cities 
in many states lawmakers have instructed public transit systems 
and utility companies to begin converting to natural gas 
last fall gm ford motor co and chrysler corp announced a 
plan to work with the nations major oil companies in investigating 
the cost of using alternative fuels the automakers along with 14 
us oil companies agreed to spend 113 million on the research 
effort 
