<DOCNO> AP900619-0235 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
world trade negotiators on tuesday tentatively 
agreed that countries should list all charges in addition to fixed 
tariffs that importers must pay 
a spokesman for the 96nation general agreement on tariffs and 
trade said the proposed measure would help importers and exporters 
by increasing the clarity of import duties 
implementation of the accord is dependent on a successful 
conclusion to the gattsponsored uruguay round of trade 
negotiations the talks are scheduled to end in december with a 
package of new rules to liberalize trade in 15 sectors including 
an agreement to cut tariffs 
according to the text of tuesdays agreement governments would 
have to list all other duties and charges in their schedules of 
bound tariff items a tariff is bound under gatt rules once a 
government gives a commitment not to increase it 
gatt members would also have to freeze these other duties and 
charges at the rates existing when negotiators reach agreement on 
a uruguay round tariff accord 
examples of such charges include fiscal taxes stamp taxes port 
improvement taxes import surcharges and landing taxes according 
to a gatt statement 
currently governments are under no obligation to publish such 
charges as a result many traders are unaware of their existence 
until they import a product bound tariffs by contrast have to be 
listed 
gatt spokesman david woods said the proposed measure would yield 
worthwhile practical results for traders 
the gatt statement said the text of the decision was based on a 
proposal submitted last year by new zealand 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

