<TEXT>
bond prices slipped tuesday in light trading as 
the market shrugged off news that growth in the nations housing 
market dropped to its slowest pace since the last recession 
the treasurys benchmark 30year bond lost 732 point or 219 
per 1000 in face amount its yield which rises when prices fall 
climbed to 847 percent from 846 percent late monday 
the market did not have the expected reaction to the commerce 
department report that housing starts fell 14 percent in may to 
the lowest level since october 1982 
usually signs of economic weakness lead to an upturn in bond 
prices on the belief that the news will prompt the federal reserve 
to lower interest rates falling rates can boost the value of 
fixedreturn investments such as bonds 
but the bond market acted perversely said robert brusca 
chief economist at nikko securities co in new york bond prices 
fell on the news 
brusca said the markets reaction may be explained by the fact 
that it already was well known that the housing market is weak 
the reaction also shows the market is more concerned with other 
factors such as upcoming economic reports that include the revised 
firstquarter gross national product thursday and durable goods and 
personal income friday and upcoming government bond auctions 
brusca said 
william sullivan director of money market research at dean 
witter reynolds inc agreed there was concern among traders about 
a possible oversupply of treasury securities the government on 
wednesday was expected to announce details of its upcoming auction 
of twoyear and fouryear notes 
the markets downward path began friday when the government 
issued a report showing industrial production rose at a 
greaterthanexpected pace in may the market interpreted the 
report to mean it was unlikely the fed would ease interest rates 
soon since the report indicated inflation may be rising 
in the secondary market for treasury bonds tuesday prices of 
shortterm governments fell from 132 point to 116 point 
intermediate maturities fell from 332 point to lsqb point and 
longterm issues fell as much as point according to telerate 
inc a financial information service 
the movement of a point equals a change of 10 in the price of a 
bond with a 1000 face value 
the shearson lehman hutton daily treasury bond index which 
measures price movements on all outstanding treasury issues with 
maturities of a year or longer fell 098 to 115729 
yields on threemonth treasury bills auctioned monday traded at 
were slipped to 798 percent as the discount fell 1 basis point to 
773 percent yields on sixmonth bills auctioned monday remained 
at 806 percent as the discount held at 764 percent yields on 
oneyear bills rose to 812 percent as the discount rose 4 basis 
points to 757 percent 
a basis point is onehundredth of a percentage point the yield 
is the annualized return on an investment in a treasury bill the 
discount is the percentage that bills are selling below the face 
value paid at maturity 
the federal funds rate the interest rate banks charge each 
other on overnight loans was quoted at 8lsqb percent down from 8 
percent late monday 
in the taxexempt market the bond buyer index of 40 actively 
traded municipal bonds fell 332 point to 91 1632 the average 
yield to maturity rose to 752 percent from 751 percent late 
monday 
